'''Manis''' was the trained [[orangutan]] that played Clyde as [[Clint Eastwood]]'s sidekick in the [[1978 in film|1978]] box office hit ''[[Every Which Way but Loose (film)|Every Which Way But Loose]]''. Its [[1980 in film|1980]] sequel, ''[[Any Which Way You Can]]'' (1980), did not feature Manis, as the "child actor" had grown too much between productions.  In the sequel two orangutans, C.J. and Buddha, shared the role.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0080377/fullcredits?ref_=tt_ql_1|title=Any Which Way You Can, Full Cast & Crew|website=IMDB}}</ref>.

Manis returned to working with his trainers' act in Las Vegas.<ref name="Gleaner">{{cite news|url=http://www.newspaperarchive.com/newspapers1/na0021/2589323/14342846.html|title=The Daily Cleaner|date=1979-09-12|work=The Gleaner|publisher=Gleaner Company|page=5|accessdate=2008-06-18}}</ref>

